  "riddle": "1. Begin your journey with a man of the stage, Michael O’Hare. Discover the year in which he first graced the world with his presence.\n\n2. Track down the metropolis where O’Hare’s stage was set, the Windy City known for its deep-dish delights and skyscrapers. How many souls resided there according to the latest tally in 2020?\n\n3. Turn your eyes eastward now. If the Big Apple had a sprawling neighbor, its numbers would be as grand, if not grander. What is the total count of inhabitants in the United States as of recent reckonings?\n\n4. There exists another city, the birthplace of American democracy. Within this historic cradle, in what year did its foundation first take hold?\n\n5. Ascend from ground level by considering how high this cradle sits above the sea. What is the elevation measured in meters?\n\n6. Among the historic cobblestones and cheese-steak aromas, count how many inns or lodges offer refuge near this place of brotherly affection.\n\n7. Consider the two counts you hold from your prior inquiries about refuges and the rise from the sea. What remains after you find the absolute difference between these values?\n\n8. With the foundation year in hand, reckon how many divisors shape this number into its form.\n\n9. Finally, piece together the elements from your quest: add together the population of the Windy City, the founding year of a democratic cradle, its elevation in meters, and the divisor count from clue 8. From this sum, unveil the single digit hidden within.",
